<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1410,2014]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,1807,1833]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Remarks</emphasis>
: Occasionally taken off the KZN coast, a few dozen specimens were landed during a short-lived deepsea fishery off Port Shepstone that also landed 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Smith" authorityYear="1949" box="[731,892,1843,1869]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dalatiidae" genus="Dalatias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squaliformes" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="licha">
<emphasis box="[731,892,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Dalatias licha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Compagno" authorityYear="1984" box="[948,1180,1843,1869]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Mitsukurinidae" genus="Mitsukurina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lamniformes" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="owstoni">
<emphasis box="[948,1180,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Mitsukurina owstoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
among other deep-sea species (D.A. Ebert &amp; P.D. Cowley, unpubl. data). The species is known to occasionally venture into shallow water, but to date no known records have been caught by the KZN Sharks Board. The first confirmed records of this species were from off 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fowler" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[495,579,1951,1977]" class="Mollusca (awaiting allocation)" family="Mollusca (awaiting allocation)" genus="Durban" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mollusca (awaiting allocation)" pageId="39" pageNumber="126" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Durban</taxonomicName>
in 
<date box="[615,771,1951,1977]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" value="1966-10">October 1966</date>
, 
<date box="[782,949,1951,1977]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" value="1968-02">February 1968</date>
, and 
<date box="[1006,1131,1951,1977]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" value="1972-04">April 1972</date>
.
</paragraph>
